1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,083
They gave us books

2
00:00:02,791 --> 00:00:05,291
Religious books and the Quran

3
00:00:05,750 --> 00:00:07,333
And newspapers issued by them

4
00:00:07,583 --> 00:00:09,500
We looked for outside news

5
00:00:09,583 --> 00:00:11,458
Though we knew it was not reliable

6
00:00:11,583 --> 00:00:14,208
The news was scarce and limited to their achievements

7
00:00:14,583 --> 00:00:16,375
So we had to read the books

8
00:00:17,083 --> 00:00:19,125
Willingly, not by force

9
00:00:19,791 --> 00:00:23,208
We also communicated with other group cells

10
00:00:23,375 --> 00:00:27,208
Through the electricity and water pipes

11
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:31,208
To ask newly arrived prisoners about outside news

12
00:00:31,708 --> 00:00:34,791
Relations were good because we were ignorant of our fate

13
00:00:35,083 --> 00:00:38,791
If death came, we were all in the same boat

14
00:00:39,416 --> 00:00:41,833
We had a small glimmer of hope

15
00:00:42,166 --> 00:00:43,875
That we might see each other outside prison

16
00:00:44,083 --> 00:00:48,583
Our relationship was good, even more than brotherly

17
00:00:48,750 --> 00:00:51,333
We refused when they offered to show us their ISIS videos

18
00:00:51,625 --> 00:00:55,208
Because all their productions showed the killing of prisoners

19
00:00:55,583 --> 00:00:56,916
As well as battles

20
00:00:57,125 --> 00:00:59,166
All scenes of killing and violence

21
00:00:59,291 --> 00:01:01,958
We had absolutely no need to see anything like that

22
00:01:02,583 --> 00:01:06,166
There was a routine every Monday and Thursday

23
00:01:06,833 --> 00:01:09,208
Fasting was obligatory

24
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:11,333
They prepared a meal

25
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:15,291
Of <i>suhur</i> [pre-dawn meal] on Wednesday night

26
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
So we could fast on Thursday

27
00:01:20,791 --> 00:01:23,708
On regular days, there were two
meals, one in the morning and another

28
00:01:23,833 --> 00:01:28,083
At or just before sunset prayer

29
00:01:29,125 --> 00:01:33,583
They sometimes left some food

30
00:01:33,791 --> 00:01:36,291
So if we got hungry at night, we could eat

31
00:01:38,208 --> 00:01:41,166
Every Friday morning

32
00:01:41,541 --> 00:01:47,333
We personally cleaned the group cell

33
00:01:47,708 --> 00:01:52,583
And the corridor between the group cells and the solitary cells

34
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:56,250
It was mandatory for the prisoners

35
00:01:56,500 --> 00:02:01,625
That two or three of them go out to clean the group cell
